    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
            <p>Not really published before <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>118800</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cassels1955"/>, p.<citedRange>34</citedRange></bibl> (mention of an inscribed base);
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p.<citedRange>218</citedRange></bibl> (diplomatic transcription from Cassels' notebook).</p>
                    <p>Additional bibliography: <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2020c"/>, p. <citedRange>318</citedRange>, n. 5 and fig. 5</bibl>;
                        <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.25</citedRange></bibl>.
                </p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Πέλεια"><supplied reason="lost">Π</supplied>έλεια</name> 
                        <persName type="attested" key=""><name type="patronymic" nymRef="Μελάνιππος">Μελανίππω</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><lem><supplied reason="lost">Π</supplied>έλεια</lem>
                <rdg resp="#dthorn-thorn2009"><space quantity="1" unit="character"/><unclear>ΕΛ</unclear>ΕΙΑ</rdg></app></p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Peleia fille de Mélanippos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Peleia daughter of Melanippos.</p>
            </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Peleia figlia di Melanippos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>بيليا ابنة ميلانيبوس</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>The feminine name <foreign xml:lang="grc">Πέλεια</foreign> was already known at 
                    Cyrene (<ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.103.html">IRCyr2020 C.103</ref>, l. 29 and <ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.129.html">IRCyr2020 C.129</ref>, l. 13) 
                    and Taucheira (<ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/T.623.html">IRCyr2020 T.623</ref>, l. 2) at later dates; no other name would match the gap.</p>
	<p/>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
